5:
I hear that the umbrella shop is
doing very well.
8:
That's right. It's great to see her
high-quality items in the hands of
more people.
11:
There's nothing worse than seeing a
product that's clearly incredible do
poorly on the market! Oh, the tears
I've shed for similar cases...
16:
Uh, it sounds like this was personal
for you, huh?
19:
Hey, you there! With the stylish
umbrella! Do you have a moment?
25:
Such an elegant design—oh, and
that fabric is simply excellent. Yes,
yes, this is incredible craftsmanship.
27:
Hear me out, Miss! Would you be
willing to model for us? I'd love to
include you in an upcoming issue.
31:
"Top 100 Fashion Trends for the New
Year."
I see... So you're a reporter for the
Oculus.
35:
Hold on a minute! You want to
include me in a fashion magazine?
And... the Top 100, of all issues?!
46:
Nope. Just hurry up and tell us
already.
50:
The Top 100 fashion issue is one of
the Oculus's most popular! They put
it out every single year around this
time.
52:
And, more importantly, the front
page of this year's edition will be
graced by none other than the
great Lady Levy!
57:
I see. So that means you'll be
featured in the same issue as your
idol, Trista! Isn't that wonderful?
62:
N-no! It's not! An inexperienced
adventurer like me has no business
being mentioned in the same
breath as her!
65:
Now, now! Don't be so hard on
yourself. You most definitely do!
Your outfit's unfamiliar yet elegant
aura is exactly what we need in our
magazine!
66:
Please, believe in yourself.
Confidence exudes radiance, after
all!
81:
Um... Regardless... If I agree to work
with you... Would I be able to get
Lady Levy's signature, by any
chance?
85:
Ah, sorry! That was terribly
inappropriate and unprofessional. I
let my impulses get the best of me!
88:
No, no. It's no problem. On the
contrary—Lady Levy would likely love
to meet you!
92: In that case, I'll do it!
99:
Ahh, what an idiot I was! How could I
just go and accept that offer
without thinking it over...
102:
What's with the change of heart?
You were over the moon when you
accepted.
106:
Well, that's true, but... I was too
caught up in the moment! Now that
I can think clearly, I realize I'm not at
all cut out for such an endeavor!
110:
Now that I think about it... Just a
while ago, I was pretending to be a
merchant! What am I even doing?
I'm an adventurer!
113:
Little late for an identity crisis, don't
you think?
118:
Hm. It's true that you're not the most
conventional adventurer out there,
yes...
120:
But who's to say that's a bad thing? I
certainly don't think it is.
123:
Huh. Didn't expect that line from you,
Light.
126:
You have your own diligent study to
thank for this, Trista. All that
knowledge you've accrued by
reading books about Yamato has
paid off!
129:
I think you should be proud of
yourself!
134: I... understand. I'll do my best!
144:
What happened? Did something go
wrong with interview?
147:
No, that's actually been going very
smoothly. I even got Lady Levy's
signature and—
152:
N-never mind! That's beside the
point. Actually, while I was there, one
of the higher-ups from the Oculus
dropped by...
155:
He seemed to be really interested in
the culture of Yamato... and he
asked me... 
If I'd be willing to publish a book
about it!
162:
Th-thank you! Wow... I can't believe
it... But wait, is this really okay?
165:
Yamato exists in an entirely
separate world, after all... I'd have to
keep quiet about the existence of
the World Flipper as well, of course...
167:
Writing a book is a huge
undertaking! Can I even do this?!
172: Do you want to do it?
177:
...Yes!
If I had the chance, I'd love to!
186:
You can just say that Yamato is a
country that exists in a far, far away
place on this world! People will be
none the wiser.
190:
We can help you gather resources.
Or, we could actually travel there
ourselves and speak to the locals!
196:
I'm still a novice adventurer, and I
know I can't hold a candle to Lady
Levy... but...
200:
I'm going to try and write the best
book on Yamato that I possibly can!
204:
Do your best, Trista. We are rooting
for you.
